:"2024-12-11T21:51:22Z","updated_at":"2024-12-11T21:51:22Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"### Description:

- transform.hough_circle_peaks returns the centers as cx, cy; it may be more consistent with the rest of the library to instead return row, col (my preference would be even to return a single (n, 2)-shape array of row, col pairs).  Fixing this would require going through the usual deprecation dance, so I'm not sure it's really worth it.
- Currently, peaks can be filtered based on the x- and the y- distance between the peaks (which may need to be renamed to r-distance and c-distance if the change above is made), but I feel that it is actually more natural to filter based on the euclidian distance between the centers (e.g. to ensure non-overlapping disks).  This could be also be fixed without breaking backcompat by providing support both for x/y-distance filtering and euclidian distance filtering.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-image/scikit-image/issues/7633/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-image/scikit-image/issues/7633/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}}

